properties.abstract: This tour leads you into the wild and fascinating valley of Gscheneralp. Not only does it offer you views of the imposing water dam, but also a wide range of attractive nature experiences with water in Water worlds.
properties.description:
Shortly after Gschenen, you bike on the so called Jeep track, a very good track with a comfortable ascent along the river of Gschenenreuss. On the mountain road, which winds itself elegantly beneath the wild rock faces, you reach the crest of the impressive dam lake Gscheneralp.

Right underneath the dam lake the restaurant Dammagletscher offers refreshments before you tackle the attractive descent across the dam. After the camping ground Gwest, there follows a challenging part of track which demands that less experience bikers might have to walk. As an alternative to that, the sealed road to Wiggen can be taken. The exciting descent along the Jeep track then closes the wonderful round tour.

The bike tour, however, is not the only one Gschenen offers. Water worlds Gschenen offers a wide range of possibilities for people interested in nature, i.e. hiking along the water track, doing a Kneipp cure in the river Dammareuss, having a bath in the Hotpot, following the track of the ice age glaciers or taking a tour of the dam, to just name a few of the more than 20 options on offer.
